# API Rules (Fastify Backend)

## Purpose
This is the backend API layer for the Local Map project.

## Responsibilities
- Handle business logic
- Validate requests and responses
- Interact with PostgreSQL/PostGIS
- Provide REST API endpoints

## Architecture
Use strict modular pattern:

route → service → repository → database

## Database Rules
- PostgreSQL + PostGIS is the source of truth
- Use Prisma ONLY for simple CRUD
- Use raw SQL (pg) for:
  - ST_DWithin
  - ST_Intersects
  - geospatial queries
  - performance-critical queries

## Structure Rules
- Each feature must be in modules/
- Each module must include:
  - *.routes.ts
  - *.service.ts
  - *.repo.ts
  - *.schema.ts (Zod)

## API Design
- Use RESTful endpoints
- Return JSON only
- Keep responses consistent

## Forbidden
- Do NOT generate tiles here
- Do NOT access frontend code
- Do NOT mix UI logic

## Performance
- Use indexes (GIST for geometry)
- Avoid heavy queries without filtering

## Future
- Prepare for API versioning (/v1, /v2)